    <div class="revenue-model-container">
        <div class="revenue-model">
            <h2>Revenue Model</h2>
            <p>This is the revenue model for <strong>Munch</strong>, our aggregate food delivery platform.</p>

            <ul>
                <li><strong>Revenue Streams:</strong> Commission fees from restaurants and delivery charges.</li>
                <li><strong>Restaurant Partners:</strong> 
                    <ul>
                        <li>Minimum commission of <strong>5%</strong> and up to <strong>20%</strong> per transaction.</li>
                        <li>Example: Vendor 20% of R100 = <span class="highlight">R20 x 500 transactions/hour = R10,000 per hour</span>. Daily earnings could be R240,000.</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li><strong>Delivery Charges:</strong> 
                    <ul>
                        <li>The platform earns 20% of the delivery fee per order.</li>
                        <li>Example: Delivery 20% of R10 = <span class="highlight">R2 x 500 transactions/hour = R1,000 per hour</span>. Daily earnings could be R24,000.</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li><strong>Pricing Strategy:</strong> 
                    <ul>
                        <li>Promo codes for customer retention and engagement.</li>
                        <li>Variable commission structure for vendors, ranging from 5% to 20% depending on transaction volume.</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
            </ul>

            <div class="example">
                <strong>Example Revenue Calculation:</strong><br>
                For 500 transactions per hour at 20% commission from vendors and delivery charges, the platform can earn up to <span class="highlight">R264,000 daily.</span>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

